    <title>mountebank v1.1 release</title>
    <id><%= version %></id>
    <updated>2014-05-02</updated>
    <content type='html'>
      <p>mountebank is happy to provide you with the following changes in v1.1</p>

      <h2>More Install Options</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>v1.0 only supported installing through npm.  mountebank now supports self-contained
        packages on all supported platforms, which do not require node.js installed on the target
        platform.  See the <a href='http://www.mbtest.org/install'>install</a> page for details.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>New Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>A new <a href='http://www.mbtest.org/docs/overview'><code>?replayable=true</code></a> query parameter to retrieve
        all imposters or a single imposter without the <code>requests</code> and <code>matches</code>
        arrays.  This supports runtime downloads of a configuration to replay later.</li>
        <li>Mass update and delete capability.  mountebank now supports PUT and DELETE verbs
        on /imposters.  This is designed to support loading a configuration file of imposters at
        runtime.  See the <a href='http://www.mbtest.org/docs/overview'>API overview</a> page.</li>
        <li>A new <a href='http://www.mbtest.org/docs/api/stubs'><code>_behaviors</code></a> field available for stubs.
        <code>_behaviors</code> currently supports adding latency to each response.</li>
        <li>A new <a href='http://www.mbtest.org/docs/commandLine'><code>--nomock</code></a> command line option to prevent
        mountebank from recording requests.  This supports long-running processes from leaking memory
        where mocking is not important.</li>
        <li>A new <a href='http://www.mbtest.org/docs/commandLine'><code>--file</code></a> command line option to
        load a configuration file at startup for creating imposters.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Documentation Improvements</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href='http://www.mbtest.org/examples'>Example usages</a> in multiple languages and multiple protocols.</li>
        <li>This ATOM feed, which will be updated with release notes on every release.  Subscribe in
          <a href='http://feedly.com/index.html#discover'>feedly</a> or your favorite RSS reader.</li>
        <li>A new <a href='http://www.mbtest.org/glossary'>glossary</a> to help explain mountebank concepts.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Bug Fixes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Fixed <a href='https://github.com/bbyars/mountebank/issues/3'>incorrect handling of JSON null values</a></li>
        <li>Fixed <a href='https://github.com/bbyars/mountebank/pull/9'>inconsistent end tags</a> on the stubs
        documentation.</li>
        <li>mountebank now support <a href='https://github.com/bbyars/mountebank/issues/4'>ints, floats, and
        booleans</a> for predicates.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Many thanks to <a href='http://nikosbaxevanis.com/'>Nikos Baxevanis</a> for help with this release.</p>
